ads.author: Carlos Ortega
ads.title: IGT Game King
ads.description: Order today and receive it before Christmas The IGT G20 Game King is a popular multi-game slot machine that features a wide variety of poker, keno, video slots, and blackjack games within a single cabinet. It is known for its sleek design, high-definition display options, and a large library of available game titles. Key Features and Specifications Display: The machine features dual 20-inch 16:9 high-definition displays, with options for standard LCD or MLD (Multi-Layer Display) technology, often utilizing greener LED backlighting. Cabinet: The G20 cabinet is a redesigned upgrade from IGT's AVP (Advanced Video Platform) and offers enhanced serviceability and a modern look. It is available in both upright and bar-top configurations. Power: The machine runs on a standard 110 V household current (or 120/240V, 4.0/2.0 Amps, depending on the variant), requiring no special wiring. It is recommended to use a power surge protector. User Interface: It typically includes an interactive touchscreen interface for easy navigation and gameplay, along with physical buttons.

ads.author: Rob Schoonmaker
ads.title: Gate Of Doom 1990 Full Size Stand Up Arcade Game
ads.description: Gate of Doom, known in Japan as Dark Seal (ダークシール), is a hack 'n slash game developed by Data East and released in 1990 for arcades. Gate of Doom is a hack 'n slash game which uses a top-down, isometric perspective. Players can choose between four different characters, each with their own characteristics and abilities. The player can move and attack in eight directions, as well as unleash a powerful spell once its accumulated enough magic power. Much like in Karnov, the player can pick between available spells by tapping the joystick left and right. Levels are filled with enemies and traps, as well as treasure chests which the player can open to obtain various items and power-ups which give passive boosts to the character.

ads.author: Tom Grizzard
ads.title: 1992 Konami X-Men video arcade (PLEASE READ COMMENTS)
ads.description: 1992 Konami X-Men video arcade game is a retro collectible arcade gaming machine that allows players to experience the popular X-Men franchise through interactive gameplay. With Konami's reputation for quality and innovation, this arcade game offers a nostalgic gaming experience for fans of the series and collectors of vintage arcade machines. Featuring the iconic X-Men characters and storyline, this video arcade game is a must-have for any gaming enthusiast looking to add a piece of arcade history to their collection. THE GOOD: Cabinet is in great overall condition. Monitor has no issues. Joysticks work fine, might be loose for some likeness/favor but nothing a new centering grommet would not solve... and not seized for removal as I did remove to clean and made adjustments, and shafts were cleaned well so wouldn't seize in near future (for easy removal). THE BAD: Original gameboard took a dump on me, and cost to replace is hovering around $1000.00... so, I installed a Pandora's DX box (turning off all games except X-men, so boots directly into game) and wiring the player 3 and player 4 control in via two "USB Joystick" pcb wiring adapters. The Pandora DX does support 4 players in Konomi X-Men with only one quirk that is not an issue... when you start either player three or player four you get player three, followed by player four... no big deal at all... besides that one super minor quirk everything works as it should. To be clear, you can play a three player or a four player game no problem, and you can pick who is each... you just get player 3 controls first regardless if you hit player 3 or player 4 start, followed by play 4 controls if you hit either player 3 or player 4 start after starting a 3 player game first. I see no sound or video issues WHATSOEVER playing X-Men on the Pandora's Box DX... NONE! As a convenience, I added 4 free-play buttons just above each of the coin chutes (small red start push buttons like on 1980's midway cocktail tables, barely noticeable) on the two top coindoors for any home user purchase.... those can easily be taken disabled and the coin mechs for all four players work fine if buyer wishes to collected revenue. Will ship via freight carrier at Buyer's expense. Local pickup allowed and encouraged (zip 31525). Local delivery (from Savannah down to Jacksonville) available for nominal fee.

ads.title: Vintage Pinball flyer Apollo13
ads.description: Vintage Pinball flyer Apollo13. Here's some information about this notable pinball machine: Release and Theme: Released in October 1995 by Sega Pinball, Inc., this machine is based on the popular movie Apollo 13. Unique 13-Ball Multiball: It's famous for being the first and only pinball machine to feature a 13-ball multiball mode, which is a key highlight in its marketing and gameplay. Gameplay Features: The machine incorporates various features to enhance the space mission theme, including a rotating moon with a magnet, a shaker motor for "earthquake-like" effects, and a rocket that launches balls during multiball modes. Collectibility: Original promotional flyers and parts for the Sega Apollo 13 pinball machine are still available for collectors. Designers: It was designed by prominent pinball designers Joe Kaminkow and Joe Balcer. For more information please call or message me. Located in Spencer Tennessee. [hidden information]. ads.author: Kenny Krm
ads.title: Auethentic real deal MEGATOUCH RX - Barside Touchscreen Arcade game (124games!)
ads.description: the real deal my son picked 2 up from a person that clears out buisnesses. This is the MEGATOUCH RX model bartop/countertop style can swivel on base -- you have seen these before - sitting on the end of a bar counter at a bar or restaurant.... and there are all sorts of mind and skill challenging games loaded 124 different games... our favorite has always been MONSTER MADNESS! it is set to free play.. but you can make it take credits. we have the key and you can open up the back to changing the settings, clean the dust out occasionally(there is a fan in there that cools the machine), update the games!, or do maintenance. Measures: 20" across in total about 18" deep in total Screen is: 16" wide 10" tall (= 19" diagonal) SO ITS PRETTY BIG! Since we have had it we have done nothing to it except play it... my son sold his off... We are parting with it because its just too dang fun! (doesnt make sense? right.. but it actually is quite addicting!) for 1 or 2 players but most games are really 1 player YOU VS THE COMPUTER! This game really makes you THINK!... anyone can play and have fun but to DO GOOD you have to think 4-5 moves ahead. .... Wordster is a game that gives you 6 letters and you have to see how many words you can make out of the 6 letters... yes makes you think! Many games are based on scoring 11 or 21... many games like the monster madness make you disassemble blocks to clear the board.. and there is strategy to it! again this is not some "fake" arcade game.. THIS IS A REAL ARCADE GAME THAT WAS ONCE IN A REAL BAR. but it was well cared for.. and not beat up... ITS GOOD CLEAN FUN!!!! and addicting! not too heavy can go in your den, on a hightop table (in our old home we had a different style of one and it was in our big kitchen on a corner hightop with 2 barstools and was "an attraction" to say the least!

ads.author: Glenn Musto
ads.title: Atari Tempest Arcade Machine – 1981 Classic Reproduction, w/ modern electronics
ads.description: Modern Re-Creation of the Legendary 1981 Atari Tempest Step back into the golden age of arcades—without the headaches of vintage hardware. This is a brand-new machine built in the style of the iconic Atari Tempest, faithfully recreating the sights, sounds, and gameplay of the original classic. Authentic Gameplay As a Tempest champion in the 1980s and owner of an original machine, I can personally vouch that the gameplay here is spot-on, indistinguishable from a brand-new Tempest as it played in arcades back in the day. Why This Machine Is Better The truth is, the original Tempest was a maintenance nightmare. Its color X-Y CRT monitor burned itself out, circuit boards constantly failed, and many machines ended up in the dump. That’s why working originals are nearly impossible to find—and even if you do, you’re stuck battling those same issues. This machine eliminates every one of those problems, while giving you more: 24" LCD with LED backlighting (IPS panel, any-angle viewing — no fragile CRT). New spinner with dual sealed bearings for silky-smooth precision control. 50-watt stereo sound system with subwoofer, volume control pod, and headphone jack (not just old mono sound). Commercial-grade power: 500+ watt ATX supply plus built-in 1,000-joule surge protector with EMI/RFI filtering. Universal JAMMA harness for plug-and-play swap of other JAMMA boards. Durable build: 3⁄4” commercial-grade cabinet, stainless steel control panel hardware, polycarbonate overlay and graphics (not scratch-prone vinyl). LED marquee lighting (no hot fluorescent bulbs). Poly wheels that roll without scratching floors. Freeplay setup for home use (no quarters required). Choice of keyed vault-style lock or thumb lock for the front door. Extra Features Tempest & Tempest Tubes — play classic levels and unlock options never before accessible. Levels 1 through 99 — explore stages you may have never reached in the arcade. Demonstration Mode: blast through tubes, clear spikes, or jump levels instantly—perfect for testing all 99 levels, whether you’re a pro or a newcomer. Why It Matters This is not just another retro cabinet with emulation slapped inside. It’s a commercial-grade, modernized Tempest machine built to last a lifetime, with gameplay so accurate that arcade veterans can’t tell the difference. Full instructions come with order, including game options, settings, default settings, etc. Defaults are: Game difficulty is Medium, Bonus Life awarded at 20,000 points, and 3 lives per game. Local pickup or buyer arranged packing and shipping. Game is located in Saint Petersburg Florida. If you want it shipped, I will make it available any time at my home for your freight company to pick it up. You must make all arrangements. Size at control panel - approx. 25" wide x 33" deep. Heigth - approx. 73" cabinet top to floor with wheels. Weight - approx. only 170 lbs. (thanks to the LCD/LED monitor). Palleted shipping weight - approx. 210 lbs.

Golden Gate (1962) and Silver Sails (1962) - These two have identical rules, just different artwork. Both have the challenging Golden Game feature. With one exception (the Circus Queen is missing its playfield glass), all games are complete and were working all the way in the summer. In addition to the machines, you'll also get: Richard Gerlitz's Bally Bingo Pinball Machine Repair Course - 11 Videos - 5 Hours of Instruction A hydraulic lift table to help move the machines Schematics and operation manuals An assortment of playfield rubbers, posts, and springs An assortment of coils and other parts Lamps/bulbs Extra balls, which are slightly larger than standard pinball balls Specialized tools and cleaners that are helpful for servicing the machines Anything else that I have that will help you enjoy this collection Pickup only. Cash only. Will not separate. Must bring manpower to load these machines into your vehicle. The machines weigh about 250 pounds each. The machines are located in my garage, so no stairs to contend with. If you'd like, I will work with a mover that you arrange and that pays me in cash at pickup.

ads.title: Boppin’ Bugs Full-Size Arcade Game – WORKS – Set to Free Play
ads.description:
For sale is a full-size commercial arcade game: Boppin\u2019 Bugs. This is a genuine coin-op arcade cabinet\u2014not a toy, not a countertop game.

The game works properly and is currently set to free play. Lights, sounds, digital score display, and gameplay all function as they should. I have a video of the game operating and can send it to serious buyers.

Condition (please read):
This is a used arcade machine and it shows its age cosmetically. Expect scuffs, wear, and cosmetic imperfections consistent with a real arcade game that was played and enjoyed. Structurally solid and fully playable. Nothing is being hidden\u2014photos accurately reflect condition.

Details:
\u2022 Full-size commercial arcade cabinet
\u2022 Works and plays correctly
\u2022 Currently set to free play
\u2022 Coin door installed (50\u00a2 mech present)
\u2022 Key included for rear cabinet
\u2022 No key for front coin mechanism
\u2022 Solid wood construction
\u2022 Great for a game room, basement, garage, church, daycare, brewery, or rec space

Pickup / Logistics:
\u2022 Local pickup only
\u2022 Large and heavy cabinet\u2014bring appropriate help and vehicle
\u2022 I can assist with basic loading, but cannot deliver or ship

Other Notes:
\u2022 Sold as-is due to age (standard for arcade equipment)
\u2022 No trades
\u2022 If the listing is up, it\u2019s still available

This is a fun, eye-catching arcade piece that still works and is a blast to play. Priced fairly at $850.
